      <biogHist id="md5-f28933f76fc75b264b14688080f7f7fe">
        <p>Medical researcher, 1949- .  Dr. Clandinin received his PhD in plant biology from the University in 1973; he served as a research associate in the Biochemistry Department from 1975 to 1976.  After spending several years at the University of Toronto as professor of Nutritional Sciences, he returned to his alma mater in 1984 to hold joint professorships in the Departments of Foods and Nutrition and Medicine.  He has published widely and received numerous awards for his research in nutrition.  In 1984 he was named an Alberta Heritage Foundation for Medical Research Scholar.</p>
      </biogHist>
